Durban - A creative gathering of Africa's most innovative minds assures a week of recognition, rewards and inspiration at the Loeries 2017, which takes place in Durban at the weekend.ADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads

The awards, organisers said in a statement, were Africa and the Middle East’s premiere initiative that recognised, rewarded, inspired and fostered creativity in the brand communication industry.

“As the highest accolade for creativity and innovation across our region, the Loeries promotes and supports creativity by helping marketers, agencies and consumers appreciate the value of ideas and fresh thinking.”

Independent Media together with partners FCB Durban were announced as finalists in the Loeries Shared Value category for the national campaign, "Racism Stops With Me".

The campaign brought young minds together to address the reality of racism in South Africa and was initiated in 2016.












